Vice President Kamala Harris spoke at the Carole Hoefener Center in Charlotte, North Carolina, addressing the Brothers of the Omega Psi Phi fraternity. She expressed gratitude for their support during the 2020 election and urged them to continue their leadership in promoting important issues. Harris emphasized the need to elect senators who will pass key legislation, such as the John Lewis Voting Rights Act and the George Floyd Justice in Policing Act. She also highlighted the importance of addressing racial bias in home appraisals, maternal health disparities, and women's reproductive rights. Harris called on the fraternity to educate and inspire others while emphasizing the significance of their role in protecting democracy and human rights. She concluded by thanking the fraternity and encouraging them to enjoy the Conclave.